    p
      b Uploaded files
    p
      | To link to uploaded files or display uploaded images, go to the 
      = link_to "upload files page", file_path
      |  and copy the "Markdown key"
      br
      | into where you want it to display on the page.
    p
      small The format of these keys follows this pattern:
    p
      span.bold.red %file/
      | 7
      span.bold.red
        | /
      | Customizable link text
      span.bold.red
        | /
    hr

    p
      b FontAwesome Pro Icons
    p
      small
        | The 
        = link_to "FontAwesome Pro", "http://fontawesome.io/icons", target: :_blank
        |   icon library is available, if you want to use a particular icon somewhere in a page.
      br
      small You can specify arbitrary CSS classes on each icon.
    p
      small
        | Some useful classes:
        ul
          li.bold.birmingham-blue birmingham-blue
          li.bold.blue blue
          li.bold.red red
          li.bold.green green
          li.bold.gray gray
          li
            span.bold far
            |   (hollow)
          li
            span.bold fal
            |  (thin)
          li
            span.bold fa-fw
            |  (fixed width)
    p
      span.bold.red %fa/
      | icon-name
      span.bold.red
        | /
    p
      span.bold.red %fa/
      | icon-name
      span.bold.red
        | :
      | css
      span.bold.red
        | /
    p
      small You can also specify layered icons, specified from bottom up, with optional CSS classes as well.
    p
      span.bold.red %fal/
      | icon-name
      span.bold.red
        | ;
      | icon-name
      span.bold.red
        | :
      | css
      span.bold.red
        | /

    p
      small These icons can also be used in links.
    p
      span.bold.red
        | [%fa/
      | users
      span.bold.red
        | :
      | red
      span.bold.red
        | /](
      | /users
      span.bold.red
        | )
    hr

